# General rules and relationships
# A city that hosts a Summer Olympics is populous.
∀x ∀y (Host(x, y) ∧ Summer(y) ∧ Olympics(y) → Populous(x))
# A city that hosts an Olympics is a capital.
∀x ∀y (Host(x, y) ∧ Olympics(y) → Capital(x))
# If a city is a national capital of a country, that country is a country and the city is populous.
∀x ∀y (NationalCapital(x, y) → (Country(y) ∧ Populous(x)))
# If a city hosted both Summer and Winter Olympics, it must have hosted both Summer and Winter Paralympics for the same year or at least be capable of hosting them.
# Simplified to: If a city hosted both Summer and Winter Olympics, it has hosted both Summer and Winter Paralympics.
∀x ( (∃y (Host(x,y) ∧ Summer(y) ∧ Olympics(y))) ∧ (∃z (Host(x,z) ∧ Winter(z) ∧ Olympics(z))) → (∃a (Host(x,a) ∧ Summer(a) ∧ Paralympics(a))) ∧ (∃b (Host(x,b) ∧ Winter(b) ∧ Paralympics(b))) )
# If something is located in a region, that region is a region.
∀x ∀y (Location(x, y) → Region(y))
# If a university is located in a place and ranks among the best in a region, that place is part of that region.
∀x ∀y ∀z (University(x) ∧ Location(x, y) ∧ Rank(x, z) → Part(y, z))
# If a city is a capital, it is located in some region, and there exists a country it is the national capital of.
∀x (Capital(x) → (∃y Location(x, y) ∧ ∃z NationalCapital(x, z)))
# Every country has a capital city.
∀x (Country(x) → ∃y Capital(y))
# If something is located in a place, that place is part of some region.
∀x ∀y (Location(x, y) → ∃z Region(z) ∧ Part(y, z))
# If a city is populous, it is located in a region.
∀x (Populous(x) → ∃y Location(x, y))
# If a region is a region, it is part of some continent.
∀x (Region(x) → ∃y Continent(y) ∧ Part(x, y))
# A city can be both a Summer and Winter host.
∀x ∀y ∀z (Host(x, y) ∧ Summer(y) → (∃z (Host(x, z) ∧ Winter(z))))
# If a city hosted the Summer Olympics, it is a populous national capital.
∀x ∀y (Host(x, y) ∧ Summer(y) ∧ Olympics(y) → (Populous(x) ∧ ∃z NationalCapital(x, z)))
# If a city hosted an event, that event is an event.
∀x ∀y (Host(x, y) → Event(y))
# If a city hosted a Summer Olympics, it is a populous national capital of a country.
∀x ∀y (Host(x, y) ∧ Summer(y) ∧ Olympics(y) → ∃z (Populous(x) ∧ NationalCapital(x, z) ∧ Country(z)))
# If a city hosted a Winter Olympics, it is a populous national capital of a country.
∀x ∀y (Host(x, y) ∧ Winter(y) ∧ Olympics(y) → ∃z (Populous(x) ∧ NationalCapital(x, z) ∧ Country(z)))
# If a city hosted a Summer Paralympics, it is a populous national capital of a country.
∀x ∀y (Host(x, y) ∧ Summer(y) ∧ Paralympics(y) → ∃z (Populous(x) ∧ NationalCapital(x, z) ∧ Country(z)))
# If a city hosted a Winter Paralympics, it is a populous national capital of a country.
∀x ∀y (Host(x, y) ∧ Winter(y) ∧ Paralympics(y) → ∃z (Populous(x) ∧ NationalCapital(x, z) ∧ Country(z)))
# If a city is a national capital, it must be populous.
∀x ∀y (NationalCapital(x, y) → Populous(x))
# If a city hosted the Olympics, it must be a capital.
∀x ∀y (Host(x, y) ∧ Olympics(y) → Capital(x))
# If a city hosted the Paralympics, it must be a capital.
∀x ∀y (Host(x, y) ∧ Paralympics(y) → Capital(x))

# A city that hosts a Summer Olympics is populous.

# If a city hosted both Summer and Winter Olympics, it must have hosted both Summer and Winter Paralympics for the same year or at least be capable of hosting them.

# If something is located in a region, that region is a region.
∀x ∀y (Location(x, y) → Region(y))

# Every country has a capital city.
